The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Alappuzha, Sept. 17 (PTI): A five-year-old girl was locked in a classroom of a primary school in Alappuzha yesterday by teachers who were unaware that she was sleeping on one of the back benches.          
	The mistake was realised an hour later when the childs mother came looking for her. School authorities said Surya was feverish when she came to school and must have moved to the back bench on feeling tired.                   
	 Madurai (PTI): Five families of Pappanam Patti village in Ramanathapuram district, who had recently converted from Hinduism to Christianity, have allegedly been ostracised by villagers for refusing to pay an annual contribution of Rs 200 to a local temple for a festival.                   
	 Kanchipuram (PTI): The Archaeological Survey of India has discovered a megalithic burial site, dating back a 2,000-years, from a village in Kanchipuram district, an official said. The ASI, which has been conducting excavations in the village since last July, has found more than 300 burial spots in the area.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): A CISF constable was arrested on Wednesday in New Delhi for allegedly duping people and collecting money by impersonating Ahmed Patel, political secretary of Congress chief Sonia Gandhi. The arrest was made after Patel filed a complaint.                   
	 Jammu (PTI): A militant hideout in Poonch district of Jammu and Kashmir was busted on Tuesday. The raid was conducted following a tip-off. A kilo of RDX, two grenades, one landmine, one AK-47 magazine and other ammunition have been recovered.                  
	 Pilibhit (PTI): Police have caught a gang allegedly involved in making fake Indian citizenship certificates for illegal Bangladeshi migrants. Acting on a tip-off, the police arrested Parmanand Majumdar, the gangs kingpin on Tuesday.                                                                                                                         
